Name: CDAActClass
Title: CDAActClass
Descriptino: A code specifying the major type of Act that this Act-instance represents.

Name: CDAActMood
Title: CDAActMood
Descriptino: A code distinguishing whether an Act is conceived of as a factual statement or in some other manner as a command, possibility, goal, etc.

Name: CDAActRelationshipType
Title: CDAActRelationshipType
Descriptino: A code specifying the meaning and purpose of every ActRelationship instance. Each of its values implies specific constraints to what kinds of Act objects can be related and in which way.

Name: CDAContextControl
Title: CDAContextControl
Descriptino: A code that specifies how an ActRelationship or Participation contributes to the context of an Act, and whether it may be propagated to descendent Acts whose association allows such propagation.

Name: CDAEntityNameUse
Title: CDAEntityNameUse

Name: CDANullFlavor

Name: CDAParticipationType
Title: CDAParticipationType
Descriptino: A code specifying the meaning and purpose of every Participation instance. Each of its values implies specific constraints on the Roles undertaking the participation. Limited to values allowed in original CDA definition

Name: CDARoleClassAssociative
Title: CDARoleClassAssociative
Descriptino: A general association between two entities that is neither partitive nor ontological.

Name: CDARoleCode
Title: CDARoleCode
Descriptino: A set of codes further specifying the kind of Role; specific classification codes for further qualifying RoleClass codes.

Name: CDASignatureCode
Title: CDASignatureCode
Descriptino: A set of codes specifying whether and how the participant has attested his participation through a signature - limited to values allowed in original CDA definition.  **Note:** CDA Release One represented either an intended (`X`) or actual (`S`) authenticator. CDA Release Two only represents an actual authenticator, so has deprecated the value of `X`.

Name: ActRelationshipAuthorizedBy
Title: ActRelationshipAuthorizedBy
Descriptino: A relationship in which the target act authorizes or certifies the source act.

Name: ActRelationshipFulfills
Title: ActRelationshipFulfills
Descriptino: The source act fulfills (in whole or in part) the target act. Source act must be in a mood equal or more actual than the target act.

Name: ActRelationshipHasComponent
Title: ActRelationshipHasComponent
Descriptino: A collection of sub-services as steps or subtasks performed for the source service. Services may be performed sequentially or concurrently.

Name: AdministrativeGender
Title: AdministrativeGender
Descriptino: The gender of a person used for adminstrative purposes (as opposed to clinical gender)

Name: EntityClassLivingSubject
Title: EntityClassLivingSubject
Descriptino: Anything that essentially has the property of life, independent of current state (a dead human corpse is still essentially a living subject.)

Name: EntityDeterminer
Title: EntityDeterminer
Descriptino: EntityDeterminer in natural language grammar is the class of words that comprises articles, demonstrative pronouns, and quantifiers. In the RIM, determiner is a structural code in the Entity class to distinguish whether any given Entity object stands for some, any one, or a specific thing.

Name: Ethnicity
Title: Ethnicity
Descriptino: In the United States, federal standards for classifying data on ethnicity determine the categories used by federal agencies and exert a strong influence on categorization by state and local agencies and private sector organizations. The federal standards do not conceptually define ethnicity, and they recognize the absence of an anthropological or scientific basis for ethnicity classification. Instead, the federal standards acknowledge that ethnicity is a social-political construct in which an individual's own identification with a particular ethnicity is preferred to observer identification. The standards specify two minimum ethnicity categories: Hispanic or Latino, and Not Hispanic or Latino. The standards define a Hispanic or Latino as a person of "Mexican, Puerto Rican, Cuban, South or Central America, or other Spanish culture or origin, regardless of race." The standards stipulate that ethnicity data need not be limited to the two minimum categories, but any expansion must be collapsible to those categories. In addition, the standards stipulate that an individual can be Hispanic or Latino or can be Not Hispanic or Latino, but cannot be both.

Name: MaritalStatus
Title: MaritalStatus
Descriptino: The domestic partnership status of a person.    *Example:*Married, separated, divorced, widowed, common-law marriage.

Name: Race
Title: Race
Descriptino: In the United States, federal standards for classifying data on race determine the categories used by federal agencies and exert a strong influence on categorization by state and local agencies and private sector organizations. The federal standards do not conceptually define race, and they recognize the absence of an anthropological or scientific basis for racial classification. Instead, the federal standards acknowledge that race is a social-political construct in which an individual's own identification with one more race categories is preferred to observer identification. The standards use a variety of features to define five minimum race categories. Among these features are descent from "the original peoples" of a specified region or nation. The minimum race categories are American Indian or Alaska Native, Asian, Black or African American, Native Hawaiian or Other Pacific Islander, and White. The federal standards stipulate that race data need not be limited to the five minimum categories, but any expansion must be collapsible to those categories.

Name: ReligiousAffiliation
Title: ReligiousAffiliation
Descriptino: Assigment of spiritual faith affiliation

Name: RoleClassAssignedEntity
Title: RoleClassAssignedEntity
Descriptino: An agent role in which the agent is an Entity acting in the employ of an organization. The focus is on functional role on behalf of the organization, unlike the Employee role where the focus is on the 'Human Resources' relationship between the employee and the organization.

Name: RoleClassRelationshipFormal
Title: RoleClassRelationshipFormal
Descriptino: A relationship between two entities that is formally recognized, frequently by a contract or similar agreement.

Name: XActRelationshipDocument
Title: x_ActRelationshipDocument
Descriptino: Used to enumerate the relationships between two clinical documents for document management.

Name: XInformationRecipient
Title: x_InformationRecipient
Descriptino: Used to represent participant(s) who should receive a copy of a document.

Name: XServiceEventPerformer
Title: x_ServiceEventPerformer
Descriptino: Clones using this x\_domain should have a name "performer".
